article.linkText: Quinerly scores 17 in Memphis' 76-52 victory against Charlotte
article.story: MEMPHIS, Tenn. -- — Jahvon Quinerly scored 17 points as Memphis beat Charlotte 76-52 on Wednesday night. Quinerly also contributed six assists and three steals for the Tigers (19-8, 8-6 American Athletic Conference). Nae'Qwan Tomlin added 16 points while going 4 of 7 from the floor, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and 7 for 8 from the line, and he also had seven rebounds. David Jones had 10 points and shot 3 for 5 (1 for 3 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free throw line. The 49ers (17-9, 11-3) were led in scoring by Igor Milicic Jr., who finished with 16 points. Robert Braswell added 13 points for Charlotte. Dishon Jackson also had 10 points and nine rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
